metadata.name: SoulSea #96
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu

metadata.name: Shape of 2 #184
metadata.description:
My second minimalist generative token is about a ’Shape of 2’. 
2 vertical sets of fine lines create ONE sculpture. The left versus the right side can be either mirrored, show similar or even oppositional expressions - depending on the generated length of the horizontal lines. A ’Shape of 2’ might remind one of a classic vase, a river or a sculpture - depending on its body language.

metadata.name: Slott #62
metadata.description:
"Slott" is the sibling project of "Luft," my previous fxhash project. New color combinations, more complex tiles, and playful symmetries.

Press [s] to save the image in 4096x4096 resolution.

By Roni Block
Made with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Make-believe #4
metadata.description:
#genuary32nd – Let's meet on this make-believe date, in this make-believe place.
I’m having déjà vu, or is it a memory?

This artwork is originally created for the genuary2023 prompt "Art Deco", using the same core algorithm as Memory Module. Made with fractal math and p5js.

Keyboard controls:
[s] Save the current view in live mode.
[1] to [8] Change resolution, 1.5K to 12K.
[g] Toggle texture.

URL params:
&aspect=[aspect ratio, eg 2]
&res=[resolution multiplier, 0.5-8]

Created by Elsif, 2023.02

metadata.name: CHX-1 #170
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.


Copyright (©) 2022 Thomas Noya
Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

◉_◉

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of François Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Rapport #109
metadata.description:
The concept of nexus is a powerful one. It speaks to the idea that everything is related and that each part is necessary to create the whole. Rapport is about the relationship these parts have, harmonious or discordant, to convey a sense of unity and purpose. You are invited to explore the details and interactions of each object in its surroundings, recognizing the immense value they all have in building greater things.

A few shortcuts are available in live mode:
1 : Toggle the view (fit screen / original size)
T : Toggle paper texture
S : Save current view
H : Re-render in high resolution

The piece might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop running chrome is recommended.

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi, 2023.

metadata.name: Dialog Box #236
metadata.description:
Dialog Box is a playful generative art project that invites viewers to engage with the concept of choice in the digital age. Inspired by the early Mac OS, the artwork presents an interface of two buttons, each symbolizing a choice steeped in 80s and 90s pop culture, from the serious to the lighthearted.

https://medium.com/@duaneking/dialog-box-by-duane-king-scott-brewer-and-adam-moliski-abab7afd3519

metadata.name: Mountain Moves #133
metadata.description:
Mountain Moves - ...kind of the logical real-time consequence of "Mountain View"
featuring different mountain formation (noise) types, different display modes
(outlines, semi outlines, no outlines, soft paint strokes)
6 color modes are still switchable. initially always 2-color modes.
on phones also uses device orientation.
 
 press 'c' ... switch color mode
 press 's' ... save png of actual resolution x3

metadata.name: Morse me #21
metadata.description:
Meta level
'Morse me' can be a call. It can just as well be sarcasm and irony about today's time, where technology should actually connect people more, but it makes them partly lonely. It also describes the artist himself.
Anyway, it's pretty cool to combine an old technology like morse code with a current one to generate art. To honor the inventor of the morse code, the release date was set to his birthday.

Technical
The parameters affect the direction of how the finished output will look and is intended to give the collector customization options so that the output is not a complete surprise. Nevertheless, there are randomly generated values which make it very unlikely to generate an exactly identical image, even though at minimum and maximum values the differences are minor and hardly detectable. As a result, images can appear the same.

Randomness
Words used in the word collection to generate the morse code and thus the pattern are chosen randomly.
A word consists of letters, a letter is in turn described by a morse code, which consists of single characters. It is randomly generated whether spaces are inserted between words, letters and characters (feature).
The roundness of the rectangles in mode Rec can take up to three different combinations, which are also chosen randomly (feature). 
For the layers in mode Rec, there are combinations where the layers can be rotated depending on their number. The combinations are chosen randomly.

Interactions
[s] save
[l] save large resolution
[u] save ultra resolution
[F12] to see the used words in the used order in the console, which were used for the morse code and generated the pattern

metadata.name: SCRIBBLERS #3
metadata.description:
Generative animated drawing inspired by mindless doodling and low-res CAD graphics. Custom physics engine made with vanilla javascript. Colors quantized with GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

Use mouse/touch to drag scribbles around and untangle them.
Press ’s’ key to save PNG (live mode only).
Screen size responsive.

metadata.name: Five Body Problems: Limhamn #38
metadata.description:
Title: Five Body Problems: Limhamn
Media: Interactive WebGL, resolution variable

A randomized composition of digital artifacts. Scans of limestone samples from Malmö, Sweden. A broken TV on the sidewalk in NYC. Original photography and textures. Stream of consciousness text. Lorenz attractors.

* Mouse to orbit. Scroll wheel to zoom.

metadata.name: Font Frenzy #11
metadata.description: Exuberant and lively piece of art crafted utilizing the ASCII art technique. This creation amalgamates an assortment of fonts and typefaces, resulting in a tumultuous, seemingly disorderly impact. The elaborate and multifaceted characteristics of the ASCII art form are accentuated in this work, where each singular character adds to the complete structure. "Typeface Turmoil" was brought to life with the aid of ChatGPT, an extensive language model developed by OpenAI, offering imaginative guidance and motivation.
